metadata.description:
Scott gives a review of the research on compositional policies so far, and presents his thoughts on this using a toy example of a lamp with a switch.

00:00 Recap of Previous Discussions
02:41 Exploring Goal-Oriented Behaviors
08:59 Hierarchy and Memory in Cortical Models
46:43 Understanding Goal States in Object Models
53:16 Behavioral Models and State Changes
01:01:36 Complexities in Modeling and Practical Examples
